  "text": "The second judgement (component) of resilience identified by [CITATION_1] is that the reaction, adaptation, or outcome will be positive. A positive reaction is one in which the individual achieves success as defined by the situation. Thus, when immigrant entrepreneurs are faced with business challenges, resiliency would help them keep striving despite the inevitable adversity and risk. In sum, resilience contains two components: it must involve risk to the individual and it must contain a positive reaction to that risk. Both of these would fit with and we would propose predict the success of immigrant entrepreneurs.",
